============================================================
EXERCISE 5 — Multi-Head Attention (the parallel conversations)
============================================================

Setup: B=1, T=3, C=8, n_head=2, head_dim=4

After linear projection: Q shape = [1, 3, 8]
After reshape + transpose: Q shape = [1, 2, 3, 4]
  Meaning: (batch=1, heads=2, tokens=3, head_dim=4)

Attention weights shape: [1, 2, 3, 3]
  (1 batch × 2 heads × 3×3 attention matrix)
Output per head shape: [1, 2, 3, 4]
After merging heads: [1, 3, 8]
Final output shape: [1, 3, 8]

>>> WHAT TO NOTICE:
    The shape journey for multi-head:
      Input X:                [1, 3, 8]
      After Q/K/V projection: [1, 2, 3, 4]  (B, n_head, T, head_dim)
      Attention weights:      [1, 2, 3, 3]
      After merging heads:    [1, 3, 8]     ← back to (B, T, C)
      Final output:           [1, 3, 8]     ← same as input!

    The input and output shapes match. This is what allows transformers
    to be stacked — the output of one block feeds cleanly into the next.
    GPT-3 does this 96 times. Same block, stacked 96 layers deep.

